description: A woman from Sandeshkhali has moved the Supreme Court for a court-monitored probe into the recent incidents including sting videos and rape complaints. The petition requested an immediate hearing regarding the Sandeshkhali issue. Justice Sengupta of Calcutta High Court is involved in the case.
title: Sandeshkhali woman moves SC, seeks probe into incidents
Bombay HC allows termination of 12-year-old’s pregnancy

description: The Supreme Court in New Delhi has requested a response from the Enforcement Directorate within a week regarding former Jharkhand chief minister Hemant Soren's challenge to his arrest in a case related to alleged land grab and money laundering. The court declined to grant immediate interim bail, setting a hearing for May 17.
title: SC seeks ED reply to Soren's plea against arrest in land scam

description: Days before he was wheeled into hospital, Sushil Modi had revealed on April 3 that he had been diagnosed with cancer six months ago and would not take part in BJP’s Lok Sabha poll campaign. “I have been battling cancer for the last six months. Now, I feel that the time has come to inform people about it. I will not be able to do anything in the Lok Sabha elections,” Sushil Modi had posted on X.
title: My valuable colleague, friend for decades: PM on Sushil Modi

description: HD Revanna, an MLA from Holenarasipura belonging to JD(S), was arrested nine days ago on charges of kidnapping a woman in KR Nagar of Mandya district. He was granted conditional bail on Monday evening by a special court for elected representatives in Bengaluru. Special judge K Gajanana Bhat instructed Revanna that he is not allowed to enter KR Nagar until further orders.
title: 9 days after arrest, Revanna granted bail in kidnap case

description: PM Modi criticized Congress for their weak stance on Pakistan and emphasized the need for dynamic leadership in national security matters, questioning the opposition's ability to make strong decisions for the country.
title: PM Modi targets Aiyar & Farooq, says his govt will make Pak wear bangles

description: Union home minister Amit Shah confidently proclaims BJP's imminent victory in the upcoming election, highlighting massive turnout and criticizing opposition leaders. Shah emphasizes PM Modi's potential third term and BJP's dedication to key issues like Uniform Civil Code and job opportunities for locals.
title: Amit Shah attacks Uddhav Thackeray for no-show at Ayodhya event

description: A political roadshow in Varanasi turned into a carnival with overflowing crowds along the 5-km route. Supporters of PM Modi wore T-shirts with slogans like 'Har Dil Mein Modi' and 'Hamar Kashi, Hamar Modi'. Muslims and people from various states joined the event, praising Modi's sincerity. Kinnar Mahamandaleshwar Hemangi Sakhi greeted Modi after deciding not to run for election.
title: With Muslims joining, roadshow becomes carnival of Kashi spirit

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Monday held a large roadshow in Varanasi and is set to file his nomination after a series of religious and political activities. Several chief ministers from BJP and NDA-governed states, along with Union ministers and important BJP members, are expected to participate in the event.
title: Modi to invoke 'Kashi Kotwal' before filing papers today

description: PM Modi kicked off the campaign for the final phase of the Lok Sabha election with a 5-km-long roadshow in Varanasi. He will file his nomination for a third term on Tuesday, following a route reminiscent of his 2019 campaign. The roadshow showcased the government's achievements over the past decade, with diverse community participation and enthusiastic support from the crowd.
title: People brave heat, come out in big numbers as Modi retraces 2019 route
Melinda to leave Gates Foundation, keeps $12.5bn for her work

description: A Delhi court on Monday granted bail to Arun Bereddy in the case of a deepfake morphed video involving Union home minister Amit Shah. Bereddy, accused of managing the 'Spirit of Congress' X account, was arrested as an 'admin' of a WhatsApp group where the fake video was first posted.
title: Accused in Shah deepfake video case gets bail

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman criticized Congress for their 'khata khat' poll promises without considering the financial implications. She highlighted the importance of fiscal responsibility and long-term development over short-term populist measures. Sitharaman emphasized the Modi government's transparent fiscal management and efficient service delivery, contrasting it with the UPA's alleged lack of clarity in government finances.
title: Nirmala Sitharaman slams Cong's 'khata khat' welfare promises

description: The overall turnout for 2019 does not include the delimited seat of Srinagar, which recorded the lowest turnout this time round, at 38%. It was, however, the best performance in the constituency (as it stood then) since 1998, when 30.1% registered voters cast their vote. In 2019, 14.4% voting was recorded. According to data available on Election Commission’s voter turnout app around midnight, the second worst polling was seen in Hyderabad, AIMIM chief Asaduddin Owaisi’s home turf, which saw 45.1% turnout, a slight improvement from 44.8% recorded in 2019. Secunderabad witnessed 48.1% voting, higher than 46.5% five years ago.
title: Dip continues: 67.3% vote in Phase 4 against 69.6% in 2019
SC dismisses plea seeking sacking of Kejriwal as CM

description: Supriya Sule, the NCP (SCP) candidate from Baramati, raised a complaint on Monday. She mentioned that the CCTV cameras at the constituency's EVM strong at Food Corporation of India godown in Koregaon Park were turned off for 45 minutes. The Election Commission of India (ECI) clarified that the CCTV system was operational and only the display unit was temporarily unavailable.
title: CCTVs off for 45 mins at Baramati EVM room: Supriya Sule

description: Abhijit Ganguly, former judge of the Calcutta High Court and BJP candidate for Tamluk, filed a petition in the High Court to dismiss the attempt to murder charge against him. The charge stemmed from a confrontation during nomination submission. Justice Sengupta to consider the petition for a hearing on Tuesday.
title: BJP’s Ganguly moves HC over murder-bid case

description: Shankari Bhattacharjee, a 55-year-old woman in Guwahati, and her family members share their challenges and aspirations for government jobs spanning over three decades. Despite qualifications and efforts, they face obstacles in securing desired positions due to unfair recruitment practices and societal issues. Their story reflects the prevalent unemployment concerns and hopes for transparency in the hiring process.
title: 'Govt should make an effort to give one job per family'

description: Voting took place in Lakhimpur Kheri, Dhaurahra, and Shahjahanpur seats without any incidents of violence reported. However, voters in Kheri faced a leopard attack. Shahjahanpur saw a decrease in turnout to 53.1% from 56.2% in 2019.
title: Leopard attack mars voting in UP's Lakhimpur Kheri, 2 hurt

description: The Election Commission is currently reviewing the responses of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) and Congress to the notices regarding alleged violations of the model code of conduct (MCC) by their prominent campaigners, Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Congress MP Rahul Gandhi. Both parties have supported the speeches of their leaders.
title: EC reviewing BJP, Cong responses on code breaches
‘Frequent flyer’ pinched valuables from cabin bags, lands in police net

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge criticized Prime Minister Narendra Modi for attempting to establish dictatorial rule in the country. He mentioned that the fear of humiliation prevented Modi from attending the Ram temple inauguration in Ayodhya. Kharge highlighted the importance of upcoming elections and urged voters to prevent the rise of a dictatorial government.
title: Did not attend Ram mandir opening fearing humiliation as I'm Dalit: Kharge

description: Particularly noteworthy is the Kedarnath shrine, which witnessed a 67% increase in footfall since its portals opened on May 10. Last year, 44,892 pilgrims visited the Himalayan shrine in the first three days, which increased to 75,139 this time. Similarly, the number of pilgrims has increased by 61% in Gangotri and 59% in Yamunotri. In Badrinath, 15,432 devotees arrived in the first two days of the yatra last year. This year, 22,690 pilgrims had visited the shrine on the first day of its opening on May 12.
title: 61% increase in Char Dham pilgrims in 1st 3 days of yatra

description: Rahul Gandhi disclosed why he chose Rae Bareli over Amethi for contesting elections, citing the deep connection of Rae Bareli with his family and the support of his mother Sonia Gandhi and grandmother Indira Gandhi. He was supported by his sister Priyanka Gandhi Vadra in his criticism of the BJP and their intentions towards the Constitution.
title: Rae Bareli is karmabhoomi of 'both my mothers': Rahul Gandhi

description: Rahul Gandhi, accompanied by his sister Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, faced a question about his marriage during a public meeting in Rae Bareli. Dodging the inquiry with humor, Rahul hinted at the possibility of marrying soon. The incident took place during his campaign visit to the constituency, where Priyanka is leading the efforts.
title: 'Ab jaldi karni padegi,' Rahul replies to query on marriage at Rae Bareli rally

description: In Bijapur, the protest is gaining momentum. Tribal rights activists plan to visit Pidiya village, around 40km from Bijapur and 470km south of Raipur, on a fact-finding mission and Maoists have issued a statement alleging that innocent villagers were killed in police action.Protesters from Pidiya village in Bijapur’s Gangaloor region, where the alleged encounter occurred, began arriving at the district headquarters on Saturday.
title: Villagers allege Bijapur encounter fake, victims were collecting tendu

description: Backlash against BJP and JJP in Haryana over MSP for farm produce and unemployment has led to election nominees facing public hostility and conflicts in rural areas. BJP and JJP candidates encountering protests and cancellations in campaign rallies. Farmers' protests affecting election campaigns aligned with demands for MSP and debt forgiveness. Congress candidates campaigning freely focusing on local issues.
title: Faced with hostility, BJP & JJP Haryana picks seek cop cover

description: A bench of Justices Hrishikesh Roy and Prashant Kumar Mishra repeatedly asked senior advocate Arvind Datar, whether the two district judges, Chirag Bhanu Singh and Arvind Malhotra, were completely ignored by the HC collegium while recommending names of judicial officers’ junior to them for appointment as HC judges. Datar said non-consideration of Singh and Malhotra, despite Jan 4 SC collegium resolution asking for reconsideration by HC collegium, resulted in ignoring their merit, seniority, and unblemished judicial track record.
title: Did HP HC collegium consider dist judges? SC seeks response

description: India and France have initiated their joint 'Shakti' combat exercise in Umroi, Meghalaya, aiming to strengthen bilateral defence cooperation and enhance peace in the Indo-Pacific region. The exercise focuses on multi-domain operations in semi-urban and mountainous terrain, involving contingents from the Rajput Regiment and the French 13th Foreign Legion Half-Brigade.
title: India, along with France, kicks off drill; will bolster Indo-Pacific ties

description: St Paul’s School in Churachandpur, which was turned into a shelter for the displaced during riots & reopened partially after Aug last year, is among top-performing institutes. It had sheltered over 100 people from Kakching district. In Class 12 board exams, the school’s success rate of 95% far exceeds Guwahati zone’s pass rate of 82%.
title: Despite losing months to violence, Manipur schools shine in CBSE exams

description: On the 16th anniversary of Jaipur serial blasts, multiple private schools in Jaipur and Lucknow received bomb threats via email, causing panic evacuations. Similar threats were recently reported in Delhi and Ahmedabad. Despite thorough searches by authorities, no explosives were found.
title: 68 schools in Jaipur and 4 in Lucknow get bomb threats

description: Karnataka High Court reverses Railway Claims Tribunal decision and grants Rs 8 lakh compensation to family of woman who died after boarding wrong train. Justice HP Sandesh points out tribunal's error in applying Indian Railways Act, rules death as 'untoward incident'.
title: HC awards Rs 8L to kin of woman who died after jumping off train

description: India has extended budgetary support of 50 million dollars to the island nation following the recent visit of Maldives foreign minister Moosa Zameer. The support is in the form of a roll-over of 50 million dollars Treasury Bill for an additional year, facilitated through the State Bank of India, Male, starting from May 13, 2024.
title: India extends budgetary support of 50m dollars to Maldives

description: India and Iran signed a 10-year contract to enhance and manage the Chabahar port terminal, granting India access to Afghanistan and Central Asia while bypassing Pakistan's denial of land access to the region. The strategic port has the potential to become a significant hub for linking landlocked countries with India's economy.
title: India, Iran ink 10-year pact to equip, operate Chabahar port
Told Modi I was ready to cook something for him, but asked if he’d eat what I made: Mamata

description: Retail inflation decreased to its lowest level in 11 months in April, driven by deflation in the fuel and light segment and reduced pressures on various other segments. However, food and beverages inflation remained high, hindering the possibility of interest rate reductions. Rural inflation stood higher at 5.4%, while urban inflation was at 4.1%.
title: 4.8%: Retail inflation hits 11-month low
Man gets news of brother’s death at booth, but stays on to cast vote
TMC-BJP clashes during polling in Bengal leave 1 dead

description: The government is planning to enforce mandatory anti-fake review norms for e-commerce companies in order to safeguard consumer interests. Consumer affairs department intends to implement QCO for online consumer reviews following unsuccessful voluntary attempt to control fake reviews. The department issued quality standards for online retailers one year ago, which banned publication of paid reviews and required disclosure of promotional content.
title: Anti-fake review norms to be mandatory for e-commerce companies

description: US private equity major Warburg Pincus is set to purchase Shriram Housing Finance for Rs 4,630 crore, marking the largest acquisition of a home loan company by a private equity fund in India. This deal represents the largest investment by Warburg in the country so far.
title: US fund Warburg to buy Shriram Housing Finance

description: The income tax department introduces a new functionality in the Annual Information Statement (AIS) allowing taxpayers to view and confirm financial data affecting taxes. Taxpayers can provide feedback on displayed transactions to ensure accuracy. CBDT states that the system is operational for data from tax deductors, collectors, and reporting entities.
title: I-T dept unveils new step to aid taxpayers

description: The Sensex experienced significant fluctuations, dropping almost 200 points before recovering and closing with a slight increase. Market sentiment is influenced by uncertainties related to polls and foreign fund selling activities. Foreign investors have sold stocks worth Rs 22,800 crore in May, while domestic investors have purchased stocks worth close to Rs 23,000 crore.
title: Election effect: Sensex swings 1k pts as FPIs keep up selling

description: Foreign funds are selling Indian equities not because of election uncertainty but because they find other markets more compelling, and D-St valuations are providing them an exit opportunity, said HSBC India CEO Hitendra Dave. On Monday, Foreign Portfolio Investors were net sellers, selling shares worth Rs 4,499 crore in the capital markets.
title: 'FPI selloff not due to poll jitters, other markets seem more attractive'

description: The Srinagar Lok Sabha constituency in Srinagar recorded a voter turnout of 36.1% on Monday, the highest since the 1996 polls. The election, post-nullification of Article 370, witnessed a three-way contest involving National Conference, PDP, and JK Apni Party candidates. Key assembly segments like Chadoora, Chrar-i-Sharief, and Kangan showed significant turnout percentages.
title: In first LS poll after 370 repeal, Srinagar voting highest since 1998

description: A 22-year-old man in London has been accused of fatally stabbing a 66-year-old Indian-origin British citizen, Anita Mukhey, while she bravely defended her handbag from a mugger in broad daylight. The incident occurred at a bus stop in Burnt Oak Broadway, Edgware. The suspect, Jalal Debella, was arrested on suspicion of murder and possession of an offensive weapon.
title: Man charged with murder after PIO grandma stabbed to death in London

description: The BCCI, in a statement, informed that the tenure of the next coach will be over 3.5 years -- July 1st, 2024, to December 31st, 2027). 'The selection process will include a thorough review of applications, followed by personal interviews and assessments of shortlisted candidates," the BCCI said.
title: BCCI invites applications for head coach job

description: Pakistan's Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif approved approximately $82.6 million for Pakistan-occupied Kashmir (PoK) to address violent protests triggered by increasing electricity tariffs, flour prices, and taxes. The protests resulted in the death of a police officer and injuries to 90 others. The turmoil presents a challenge to Pakistan's military with a substantial presence in the area.
title: Pakistan clears cash to calm PoK

description: Already qualified Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) on Monday secured a top-two spot in the IPL playoffs following a washed-out match against the Gujarat Titans in Ahmedabad. The game's abandonment due to rain ensured that KKR, who now have 19 points with a match to go against Rajasthan Royals, gained one point to finish in the upper echelons of the league table. The achievement means that KKR now have an advantage of going into the playoffs, with a chance to go directly into the final.
title: KKR confirm top-two finish in IPL playoffs

description: OpenAI launches GPT-4o, offering GPT-4-level intelligence with improved text, voice, and vision capabilities. CEO Sam Altman emphasizes accessibility for all users, breaking from the paid model to make advanced AI tools available to everyone.
title: OpenAI launches GPT-4o flagship AI language model for ChatGPT

description: Gujarat Titans' aspirations for qualifying for the Indian Premier League playoffs were dashed on Monday when rain forced their must-win match against Kolkata Knight Riders to be abandoned without a single ball being bowled. As a result, KKR secured a top-two finish with 19 points from 13 games and a spot in the Qualifier 1. Meanwhile, GT, the runners-up from last year and champions of 2022, are eliminated from playoff contention, accumulating 11 points from 13 matches.
title: IPL: GT eliminated after rain washes out KKR clash

description: Former Bihar deputy chief minister Sushil Kumar Modi, aged 72, passed away after battling cancer. Won't help in elections. BJP mourns the loss of a warrior. Vijay Kumar Sinha praises Modi. May God give strength to Modi's family.
title: Sushil Modi, former Bihar deputy CM, passes away at 72

description: Melinda French Gates said Monday she was leaving the philanthropy mega foundation that she established with her ex-husband, Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates. The foundation, established with the vast wealth that the couple acquired through the success of Microsoft, is one of the most influential in global philanthropy, with a focus on preventable diseases and child poverty.
title: Melinda Gates to resign from philanthropy group founded with Bill Gates

description: Maharashtra sees surge in KP.2 cases surpassing JN.1. FLiRT variant labeled KP.2 dominant in the US. Symptomatic patients resemble previous variants. KP.2 more infectious but not severe. Precautions advised to reduce transmission risk.
title: Is Covid-19 subvariant FLiRT dangerous? Here's all you need to know

description: Rajat Patidar's dynamic half-century and impressive bowling performance were instrumental in RCB securing their fifth consecutive victory, greatly enhancing their hopes for a playoff spot with a commanding 47-run win over Delhi Capitals on Sunday. RCB set a challenging target of 187-9, with Cameron Green's unbeaten 32 off 24 balls making a significant contribution to their innings. In response, RCB's bowlers dismantled Delhi Capitals' batting lineup, limiting them to 140 runs in 19.1 overs.
title: Ganguly removes cap before shaking hands with Virat

description: Canada gears up for 'Citizenship Week' with Immigration Minister Marc Miller highlighting the importance of reflecting on Canadian identity, Indigenous Peoples' role, and faster citizenship application processing for new citizens.
title: Canada welcomed 3.9 lakh new citizens in fiscal ended March, '24

description: Viral video of diesel-fried Paratha shocks viewers, sparking health concerns. User reactions question food standards and licensing, emphasizing the need for adherence to regulations. The video and the idea behind this recipe comes as a shock because only few days before ICMR-NIN has released dietary guidelines for Indians of all age groups.
title: Video of a man cooking paratha in diesel goes viral; netizens tag FSSAI

description: As Chandrasekaran already chairs several key Tata group companies, his appointment as chairman of Tata Electronics underscores the importance of the semiconductor business to the conglomerate.
title: Chandra to chair Tata Electronics with $14 bn focus semiconductors

description: India and Iran on Monday signed a 10-year contract to develop and equip the strategic Chabahar port in Iran as India seeks to grow trade in west and central Asia. The agreement will give India 10-year access to use the port, located close to Iran's southeastern border with Pakistan, according to Iran's Ministry of Roads and Urban Development.
title: India inks 10-year deal to operate Iran's Chabahar port
Anant Ambani's Vantara lauded for timely rescue of ailing elephant, calf in Tripura

description: President Vladimir Putin's nomination of top economic official Andrei Belousov as defence minister is a sign of the importance the Russian leader places on the war economy in gaining the upper hand in what he expects will be a long conflict against Ukraine, analysts say. It is unclear if outgoing defence minister Sergei Shoigu's move to head the national security council is a demotion, while the future of its previous chief Nikolai Patrushev, a shadowy but powerful figure and an ardent hawk, is also murky.
title: Why Putin has appointed an economist as defence minister

description: The talented wicket-keeper batsman, Jos Buttler, has bid farewell to the ongoing Indian Premier League (IPL) as he prepares to join the England squad for the upcoming T20 World Cup. Ahead of the highly anticipated tournament, England is set to engage in a four-match T20I series against Pakistan, commencing on May 22, with Buttler assuming the role of captain for the Three Lions against the Green Shirts.
title: 'Facetime me with the trophy': Buttler to RR

description: Fans speculate about Urfi Javed's edited bald selfie, eagerly anticipating her appearance in Love Sex Aur Dhokha 2. Her bold persona and potential for lead roles garner praise from fans and directors alike.
title: Urfi Javed's bald selfie sparks controversy; shocked fans spot truth

description: Virat Kohli, currently the leading run-scorer in the ongoing IPL, has amassed 661 runs from 13 innings at an impressive strike rate of 155.16. Despite being placed fifth in the table with 12 points, RCB remain in contention for the playoffs. Former India off-spinner Harbhajan Singh's endorsement of Kohli's leadership stems from his exceptional performance on the field, coupled with his qualities as a leader.
title: 'RCB should bring Kohli back as captain': Harbhajan

description: Lucknow Super Giants assistant coach Lance Klusener on Monday played down team owner Sanjiv Goenka's public outburst on their skipper KL Rahul, terming it "storm in a tea cup" and said he didn't find any issue in a "robust discussion between two cricket lovers".
title: LSG downplay owner Goenka's outburst on Rahul
'FBI seized cellphones of Indian crew onboard Dali'
Sex videos case: HD Revanna granted bail by a special court
FBI warns of extortion scheme targeting Indians, businesses
PM Modi holds mega roadshow in Varanasi

description: Securing five wins on the trot, RCB are right back in the hunt for a play-off spot, and the rampant side looks like a serious threat to other teams vying for the third and fourth slots. The RCB's winning run has been lauded by many and former India pacer Zaheer Khan also joined the bandwagon, hailing the side for an unbelievable turnaround in the second half of the league.
title: RCB's stunning turnaround: 'Doesn't happen without...'
India, France kick off combat exercise; will bolster Indo-Pacific cooperation

description: April 2024 CPI Inflation: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) inflation for the month of April eased to 4.83%. The rural inflation was reported at 5.43% and urban inflation came in at 4.11%. The CPI inflation for the month of March 2024 stood at 4.85%.
title: April CPI inflation eases to 4.83% vs 4.85% in March 2024

description: Pakistan rebounded from their unexpected defeat in the series opener to clinch a convincing seven-wicket win against Ireland in the second Twenty20 match held in Dublin, setting the stage for a decisive showdown. Ireland's victory by five wickets in the T20 opener on Friday stunned Pakistan, marking Ireland's inaugural T20 triumph over their opponents.
title: Afghan fan misbehaves with Pak pacer Shaheen Afridi

description: OpenAI's Spring Update event introduces major upgrades to ChatGPT and GPT-4, teasing new features like AI voice assistant and potential phone call capabilities. Event strategically timed before Google I/O.
title: ChatGPT, GPT-4 updates, more OpenAI may announce

description: Shehbaz Sharif, the Prime Minister of Pakistan, has stepped down from his role as President of the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N). He has officially submitted his resignation to Nawaz Sharif, the leader of the PML-N. As a result of this development, the PML-N has set a general council gathering in Lahore for May 28 to choose a new president. Initially, the party had intended to convene this meeting on May 11.
title: Pak PM Shebaz resigns as PML-N chief, makes way for brother Nawaz
Mumbai: Car parking lift collapses, several injured

description: 'Kannappa', a Telugu mythological fantasy film, directed by Mukesh Kumar Singh, stars Vishnu Manchu with a star-studded ensemble cast. The teaser will be launched at the Cannes International Film Festival on May 20.
title: 'Kannappa teaser at the Cannes Festival on May 20

description: Want to buy a refrigerator under 40000 for your home online? We have a list of some of the best picks that you can consider along with the pros and cons of these refrigerators to help you compare the available options properly.
title: Best refrigerators under 40k: Top mid budget options

description: With injury issues, Punjab Kings batting all-rounder Liam Livingstone had missed games against Kolkata Knight Riders and Chennai Super Kings before returning for the game against Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Livingstone went on to score a duck in his final game against RCB.
title: Livingstone's 'IPL done' after PBKS knocked out

description: Mumbai and surrounding areas are witnessing thunderstorm activities which is expected to last for about an hour and half, according to Mumbai IMD chief Sunil Kamble. IMD also predicted the p​ossibility of hail at isolated places and advised residents to take precautions while moving out. ​​
title: Navi Mumbai, Thane hit by dust storm, rain

description: Maldives receives USD 50 million budget support from India through a Treasury Bill rollover, acknowledging India's significant assistance in infrastructural projects and grants amidst strained bilateral ties.
title: Maldives thanks India for $50m 'vital budgetary support'

description: Zomato's Q4 profit of Rs 175 crore marked a significant turnaround. Revenue reached Rs 3,562 crore, missing estimates. Blinkit achieved EBITDA positivity, but Zomato's stock declined over 7% on NSE.
title: Zomato reports Rs 175 crore profit vs Rs 188 crore loss YoY

description: The Income Tax Department streamlines ITR filing for FY 2023-24 with various utilities. Taxpayers have until July 31, 2024, to file returns. Different utilities cater to diverse taxpayer needs, offering online, offline, or Excel-based options.
title: 3 updated utilities available for ITR-3; here’s how to choose right one

description: ​​Gandhi claimed that the Modi government has waived loans amounting to Rs 16 lakh crore for a handful of top industrialists, equivalent to 24 years of MGNREGA funding and highlighted the contributions of his grandmother Indira, father Rajiv, and mother Sonia in improving the lives of Rae Bareli's residents. The constituency, considered a Gandhi family stronghold, has been represented by Sonia since 2004 and was previously held by former prime ministers Indira Gandhi and Rajiv Gandhi.
title: My family works for Rae Bareli, PM Modi for Adani-Ambani: Rahul

description: Maharashtra detected 91 KP.2 cases, predominant in Pune. Dr. Rajesh Karyakarte noted no surge in severe cases despite KP.2 spread across multiple cities, part of the FLiRT variant group.
title: Maharashtra records 91 cases of new Covid subvariant 'FLiRT'

description: S Jaishankar on Monday said that India has not received any information that is specific and worthy of investigation by its probe agencies regarding the fourth arrest made by Canada in connection with the killing of Khalistan separatist and designated terrorist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. This comes following the arrest of Amardeep Singh, a 22-year-old resident of Brampton, Surrey, and Abbotsford areas in Canada on May 11.
title: Nijjar killing: 'Nothing worthy of being probed,' says Jaishankar

description: Chennai Super Kings (CSK) took a step closer to the IPL 2024 playoffs with their five-wicket win over Rajasthan Royals on Sunday at home, which was their last game at the MA Chidambaram Stadium this season and possibly the last in Chennai as a player for the iconic MS Dhoni.
title: 'Temples will be built for Dhoni, the God of Chennai'

description: The intense burst of radiation from the Sun, one of the most powerful this year, has the potential to disrupt radio communications, navigation systems, and electrical grids on Earth. The flare has also led to stunning auroral displays, visible much farther than usual, lighting up the skies from the United States to Tasmania and captivating observers across the globe.
title: 'How Sun could wreak havoc on Earth in 8 minutes'

title: IT min shares video of Apple CEO Tim Cook for Monday motivation

The video shows the BJP candidate requesting Muslim women in the booth to remove their Burkhas, identify themselves, and check their voter identity cards.
title: BJP's Madhavi Latha checks voter IDs of burqa-clad women

title: 85% of SBI’s hiring for POs & associates are engineering graduates

description: In a video posted by KKR on social media, the upbeat mood of the squad was evident. The two-time champions became the first team to book a place in the playoffs after their win over Mumbai Indians in their last match. KKR have 18 points from nine wins in 12 matches and sit on top of the IPL 2024 table
title: Watch: 'Dhoni bhai ka ghar dikh raha hai kya?'

description: Class 10 CBSE results are finally here! Check your scores online today, May 13th, 2024, on the CBSE website (https://www.cbse.gov.in/) or the UMANG app. The website might be slow due to high traffic, so be patient. Stay tuned for updates on the national pass percentage. Congrats to all Class 10 graduates!
title: CBSE class 10 board exam results; girls outshine boys by 2.04%

Hemant Soren's counsel Kapil Sibal said his case is covered by the Arvind Kejriwal order.​​​​ Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal was granted interim bail till June 1 by Supreme Court on May 10. The Supreme Court rejected the AAP leader's plea for bail till the counting of votes on June 4.
title: Hemant Soren cites Kejriwal's bail, seeks release for poll campaign

description: Former Australian cricketer Tom Moody praised Royal Challengers Bengaluru for their performance in IPL, particularly highlighting the resurgence led by Virat Kohli. The team has a realistic chance of reaching the playoffs amid intense competition. RCB will play their final league game at the M. Chinnaswamy Stadium on Saturday against MS Dhoni's Chennai Super Kings, who are also in the running for a playoff berth.

description: At least four schools in Jaipur, Rajasthan, received bomb threats via email on Monday. Students and staff members have been evacuated, and police teams, along with bomb and dog squads, have reached the schools. Jaipur Police Commissioner Biju George Joseph confirmed the threats and mentioned that the police are working to determine the sender of the emails.

description: Demonstrations in Andhra Pradesh demand cash for votes, ranging from Rs 1,000 to Rs 6,000. Inflation drives prices up. Voting in 175 assembly and 25 LS seats on Monday. Protests in Vijayawada, Amaravati. Corruption concerns highlighted.

description: RCB secured a resounding 47-run victory against Delhi Capitals on Sunday, a triumph that not only rejuvenated their playoff aspirations but also etched a record in the 2024 edition of the Indian Premier League history. title: RCB set IPL 2024 record with win over Delhi Capitals

description: Recent online trends have surfaced, featuring short videos that tap into nationalistic sentiments by showcasing foreign admiration for China, particularly from young Russian women named Natasha and Sofia. These videos depict them speaking fluent Mandarin and praising Chinese culture, while criticizing Russian men as "drunk and lazy." They laud Chinese societal and technological progress and express a desire to adopt traditional domestic roles, such as cooking and child-rearing, in a marriage with a Chinese man.
title: 'Why young Russian women want to marry Chinese men'

description: In a shocking incident at the Paras Tierra Society in Sector 137, Noida, a lift malfunctioned in tower 5, ascending rapidly and crashing through the roof of the top floor. Two delivery personnel and a tenant were in the lift when the accident occurred. This incident echoes a previous tragedy in tower 24, where an elderly woman lost her life in a similar mishap.
title: At Noida housing society, lift breaks down & smashes into roof

description: India is set to sign a significant deal with Iran to manage Chabahar Port for the next decade, a move with far-reaching implications for the region. This diplomatic gesture comes amidst a busy election period and aims to strengthen India's connectivity to Afghanistan, Central Asia, and the larger Eurasian region, bypassing Pakistan's Gwadar port and China's Belt and Road Initiative.
title: India to sign Chabahar port pact with Iran; to counter Pak, China

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru's winning streak enhances their IPL playoff chances. Various teams have different probabilities of finishing as toppers or within the top four on points.
